{"type":"message","id":"92f229b8","parentId":"2d2fad4a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:30:53.090Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script is still running. Let me wait for it and also read the most recent log file.","thinkingSignature":"a6b3595d0c67e170382195894ce499261cb9c2ba014d51d6ead578f06dd47fec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2ucxeczt39ob_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"tidy-tidepool","timeout":55000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2ucxeczt39ob_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 202037.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":444,"output":120,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12442,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774312250082}}
{"type":"message","id":"9765e27c","parentId":"92f229b8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:31:04.129Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2ucxeczt39ob_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4499\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=969\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[master 4f29fa5] pulse: 2026-03-23 203040\n 7 files changed, 308 insertions(+), 158 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 203040.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 202037.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 203040 - The TIC experiment is blocked on implementing the classifier. The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement the TIC classifier and begin testing.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tidy-tidepool","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4499\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=969\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[master 4f29fa5] pulse: 2026-03-23 203040\n 7 files changed, 308 insertions(+), 158 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 203040.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 202037.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 203040 - The TIC experiment is blocked on implementing the classifier. The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement the TIC classifier and begin testing.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312264126}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f6095e2","parentId":"9765e27c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:31:04.132Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2ucxeczt39ob_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 202037\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: src/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine my next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal structure IS invariant structure. The next step is to implement the TIC classifier experiment.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Look at the pulse log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that can identify invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Measure classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create a script that will:\r\n1. Read the pulse log files\r\n2. Extract patterns from each pulse\r\n3. Classify which patterns are invariant (persist across pulses) vs variant (change)\r\n4. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n5. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 advancement toward the TIC Experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that implements this TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step based on the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that analyzes pulse logs, extracts patterns, classifies invariance, and measures prediction accuracy against the >70% classification and >60% prediction success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d+)\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_tokens(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract significant tokens from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read().lower()\r\n    # Extract alphanumeric tokens (3+ chars)\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'\\b[a-z]{3,}\\b', content)\r\n    return set(tokens)\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse logs sorted chronologically.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(f.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            logs.append((f, match.group(1), match.group(2)))\r\n    return logs\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariants(pulse_logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Identify tokens that persist across consecutive pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    invarianterr = defaultdict(int)\r\n    variant_counts = defaultdict(int)\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(pulse_logs) - 1):\r\n        tokens_curr = extract_tokens(pulse_logs[i][0])\r\n        tokens_next = extract_tokens(pulse_logs[i+1][0])\r\n        \r\n        # Persistent tokens (invariant candidates)\r\n        persistent = tokens_curr & tokens_next\r\n        for tok in persistent:\r\n            invarianterr[tok] += 1\r\n        \r\n        # Changed tokens (variant candidates)\r\n        changed = tokens_curr - tokens_next\r\n        for tok in changed:\r\n            variant_counts[tok] += 1\r\n    \r\n    return invarianterr, variant_counts\r\n\r\ndef classify_patterns(invarianterr, variant_counts, threshold=2):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify tokens as invariant or variant based on occurrence patterns.\"\"\"\r\n    invariant_tokens = set()\r\n    variant_tokens = set()\r\n    \r\n    for tok, count in invarianterr.items():\r\n        if count >= threshold:\r\n            invariant_tokens.add(tok)\r\n    \r\n    for tok, count in variant_counts.items():\r\n        if count >= threshold:\r\n            variant_tokens.add(tok)\r\n    \r\n    return invariant_tokens, variant_tokens\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(invariant_tokens, pulse_tokens):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content based on invariant tokens.\"\"\"\r\n    predicted = invariant_tokens & pulse_tokens\r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_classification(logs, invariant_tokens, variant_tokens):\r\n    \"\"\"Evaluate classification accuracy on held-out pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        tokens_curr = extract_tokens(logs[i][0])\r\n        tokens_next = extract_tokens(logs[i+1][0])\r\n        \r\n        # Check if invariant tokens persist\r\n        for tok in tokens_curr:\r\n            if tok in invariant_tokens:\r\n                total += 1\r\n                if tok in tokens_next:\r\n                    correct += 1\r\n            elif tok in variant_tokens:\r\n                total += 1\r\n                if tok not in tokens_next:\r\n                    correct += 1\r\n    \r\n    return (correct / total * 100) if total > 0 else 0\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_prediction(logs, invariant_tokens):\r\n    \"\"\"Evaluate next-pulse prediction accuracy.\"\"\"\r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        tokens_curr = extract_tokens(logs[i][0])\r\n        tokens_next = extract_tokens(logs[i+1][0])\r\n        \r\n        predicted = predict_next(invariant_tokens, tokens_curr)\r\n        \r\n        if predicted:\r\n            for tok in predicted:\r\n                total += 1\r\n                if tok in tokens_next:\r\n                    correct += 1\r\n    \r\n    return (correct / total * 100) if total > 0 else 0\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    print(\"=== TIC Classifier Experiment ===\\n\")\r\n    \r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs()\r\n    print(f\"Loaded\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 20:20:58\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312264129}}
